<center>
   <br><br>
   <h1>JDBC vs ODBC</h1>
   <br>
</center>
<font size=4>
<ul>
   <li>ODBC was created to become the universal standard to access
       databases on Windows platforms.</li>
   <li>Written in C and requires intermediate APIs to connect to other
       database languages.</li>
   <li>Overly complex.</li>
   <li>JDBC comes equipped with transformation features that maps JDBC
       calls to ODBC calls.</li>
</ul>
</font>
